1 Introduction

Email from Baydoun, May Ahmad on Aug 1, 2023.

Instructions in Mayâs email

I hope you are doing well and enjoying the summer. I would like to invite you to contribute to a new UKB manuscript that we are now working on. I just completed and reviewed the analysis and typed most of the Tables. I am attaching some of the Figures I have. I wanted to see if you could re-do the left hand side heatmap in Figure 3 (See powerpoint) using the new excel sheet that I am attaching here. This is very similar to the previous paper, but instead of hospital-treated infections we are looking at periodontal disease. There are many results in common, which is very interesting, including GDF-15 being among the top hits with highly significant mediation! In this case, there are 18 top hits for proteins strongly related to the exposure (periodontal disease), but only a few are real mediators between periodontal disease and all-cause dementia.

3.1 Convert to wide format

beta value

Show the code 
d_wide <-
  d |> 
  select(fourwaydecomp, beta, protein, p) |> 
  pivot_wider(
    id_cols = protein,
    # id_cols = c(protein, p),
    names_from = fourwaydecomp,
    values_from = beta
  )

p value

Show the code 
d_wide_p <-
  d |> 
      mutate(
      p_anno = case_when(
         p <= 0.001 ~ "***",
         p <= 0.01 ~ "**",
         p <= 0.05 ~ "*",
         .default = ""
      )
   ) |> 
  select(fourwaydecomp, beta, protein, p_anno) |> 
  pivot_wider(
    id_cols = protein,
    # id_cols = c(protein, p),
    names_from = fourwaydecomp,
    values_from = p_anno
  )

3.2 Convert to matrix

beta

Show the code 
# Convert to matrix
mat <-
  d_wide |> 
  select(- contains("pct_")) |> 
  column_to_rownames("protein") |> 
  as.matrix()

# Order the columns by their means
mat <- mat[, order(colMeans(mat), decreasing = TRUE)]

4 Heatmap

4.1 Row ordering

Show the code 
# o1 = seriate(dist(mat), method = "OLO")
# o1 = seriate(dist(mat), method = "MDS")
o1 = seriate(dist(mat), method = "MDS_angle")

4.2 Use full names as matrix column names

Show the code 
# abbr. name = full name
ef_name <- c("tereri" = "total effect", 
             "ereri_cde" = "controlled direct effect",
             "ereri_pie" = "pure indirect effect",
             "ereri_intmed" = "mediated interaction",
             "ereri_intref" = "interaction reference")

colnames(mat) <-  ef_name[colnames(mat)]

4.3 Make heatmap

  • p value annotation.
    • p <= 0.05: *
    • p <= 0.01: **
    • p <= 0.001: ***

Scheme I

  • Color: RColorBrewer, RdYlBu
Show the code 
# col_fun = colorRamp2(c(-2, 0.1, 2), brewer.pal(3, "RdYlBu"))
# brewer.pal(3, "RdYlBu") |> 
#    scales::show_col()
# col_fun = colorRamp2(c(-0.002, 0.2, 1.3), brewer.pal(3, "RdYlBu"))
col_fun = colorRamp2(c(-0.002, 0.02, 0.2), brewer.pal(3, "RdYlBu"))

mat |> 
  Heatmap(
   name = "Beta",
   cluster_columns = FALSE,
   cluster_rows = FALSE,
   row_order = get_order(o1),
   
   # color function
   col = col_fun,
   
   # Title
   row_title = "Protein",
   row_title_side = "left",
   column_title = "Effect size (Regression coefficients)",
   column_title_gp = gpar(fontsize = 20, fontface = "bold"),
   
   # Names
   row_names_side = "left",
   column_names_gp = gpar(fontsize = 12, fontface="bold"),
   column_names_rot = 45,
   
   # Add "*" for significant p values
   cell_fun = function(j, i, x, y, w, h, col) { # add text to each grid
        grid.text(mat_p[i, j], x, y)
    }
  )

Scheme II

  • Color: scales::hue
Show the code 
# col_fun = colorRamp2(c(-0.002, 0.02, 0.2), brewer.pal(3, "RdYlBu"))

# col_fun = colorRamp2(c(-0.02, 0.3, 1.3), brewer.pal(3, "RdYlBu"))

## data reorganizing

### Convert to wide format

beta value

```{r}
d_wide <-
  d |> 
  select(fourwaydecomp, beta, protein, p) |> 
  pivot_wider(
    id_cols = protein,
    # id_cols = c(protein, p),
    names_from = fourwaydecomp,
    values_from = beta
  )

glimpse(d_wide)
```

p value

```{r}
d_wide_p <-
  d |> 
      mutate(
      p_anno = case_when(
         p <= 0.001 ~ "***",
         p <= 0.01 ~ "**",
         p <= 0.05 ~ "*",
         .default = ""
      )
   ) |> 
  select(fourwaydecomp, beta, protein, p_anno) |> 
  pivot_wider(
    id_cols = protein,
    # id_cols = c(protein, p),
    names_from = fourwaydecomp,
    values_from = p_anno
  )

glimpse(d_wide_p)
```


### Convert to matrix

beta

```{r}
# Convert to matrix
mat <-
  d_wide |> 
  select(- contains("pct_")) |> 
  column_to_rownames("protein") |> 
  as.matrix()

# Order the columns by their means
mat <- mat[, order(colMeans(mat), decreasing = TRUE)]

glimpse(mat)
```

p value

```{r}
# Convert to matrix
mat_p <-
  d_wide_p |> 
  select(- contains("pct_")) |> 
  column_to_rownames("protein") |> 
  as.matrix()

# Order the columns according to mat
mat_p <- mat_p[, colnames(mat)]

glimpse(mat_p)
```

### Make heatmap

- p value annotation. 
  - p <= 0.05: *
  - p <= 0.01: **
  - p <= 0.001: ***

#### Scheme I

- Color: RColorBrewer,  RdYlBu
<!-- - Range: -0.02, 1.3 -->

```{r}
#| fig-height: 10
#| fig-width: 10

# col_fun = colorRamp2(c(-2, 0.1, 2), brewer.pal(3, "RdYlBu"))
# brewer.pal(3, "RdYlBu") |> 
#    scales::show_col()
# col_fun = colorRamp2(c(-0.002, 0.2, 1.3), brewer.pal(3, "RdYlBu"))
col_fun = colorRamp2(c(-0.002, 0.02, 0.2), brewer.pal(3, "RdYlBu"))

mat |> 
  Heatmap(
   name = "Beta",
   cluster_columns = FALSE,
   cluster_rows = FALSE,
   row_order = get_order(o1),
   
   # color function
   col = col_fun,
   
   # Title
   row_title = "Protein",
   row_title_side = "left",
   column_title = "Effect size (Regression coefficients)",
   column_title_gp = gpar(fontsize = 20, fontface = "bold"),
   
   # Names
   row_names_side = "left",
   column_names_gp = gpar(fontsize = 12, fontface="bold"),
   column_names_rot = 45,
   
   # Add "*" for significant p values
   cell_fun = function(j, i, x, y, w, h, col) { # add text to each grid
        grid.text(mat_p[i, j], x, y)
    }
  )
```
